bug: private_key_jwt method not supported for custom nextauth provider

### Describe the bug

I am trying to configure Ping Federate OAuth provider to my langfuse self-hosted deployment in AWS.
The error I get, when i click the button to login using the OAuth provider, is 
```
[next-auth][error][OAUTH_CALLBACK_ERROR]
https://next-auth.js.org/errors#oauth_callback_error no client jwks provided for signing a client assertion with {
	error: Error [OAuthCallbackError]: no client jwks provided for signing a client assertion with
	at async k (.next/server/pages/api/auth/[...nextauth].js:1:2293) {
		code: undefined
	},
	providerId: 'custom',
	message: 'no client jwks provided for signing a client assertion with'
}
```
The message implies that langfuse does not pass the private jwk via the auth wrapper to next auth provider, which might be true by looking at the https://github.com/langfuse/langfuse/blob/03b736ef4acab331d33824edfb497c74b7412a9f/web/src/server/auth.ts#L176-L198

### Steps to reproduce

1. Use AWS ECS Fargate deployment
2. Use `private_key_jwk` as auth method
3. JWK alg RS512

Fargate task configuration (env vars)
```json
"environment": [
	{
	  "name": "AUTH_CUSTOM_CLIENT_ID",
	  "value": "myclientid"
	},
	{
	  "name": "AUTH_CUSTOM_NAME",
	  "value": "Login using Ping Federate"
	},
	{
	  "name": "AUTH_CUSTOM_ALLOW_ACCOUNT_LINKING",
	  "value": "true"
	},
	{
	  "name": "AUTH_CUSTOM_ISSUER",
	  "value": "https://pingfederate.mydomain.com"
	},
	{
	  "name": "AUTH_SESSION_MAX_AGE",
	  "value": "600"
	},
	{
	  "name": "AUTH_CUSTOM_CLIENT_AUTH_METHOD",
	  "value": "private_key_jwt"
	},
	{
	  "name": "AUTH_CUSTOM_CHECKS",
	  "value": "state,pkce"
	},
	{
	  "name": "ENTERPRISE_SSO_REQUIRED_MESSAGE",
	  "value": "true"
	},
	{
	  "name": "NEXTAUTH_URL",
	  "value": "https://langfuse.mydomain.com"
	},
],
"secrets": [
	{
	  "name": "NEXTAUTH_SECRET",
	  "valueFrom": "arn:aws:secretsmanager:eu-central-1:000000000000:secret:nextauthsecret-XYZ123"
	},
	{
	  "name": "AUTH_CUSTOM_CLIENT_SECRET",
	  "valueFrom": "arn:aws:secretsmanager:eu-central-1:000000000000:secret:credentialsecret-XYZ123"
	}
],
```

Contents of the secret injected into `AUTH_CUSTOM_CLIENT_SECRET`
```json
{
  "d": "***",
  "dp": "***",
  "dq": "***",
  "e": "AQAB",
  "kty": "RSA",
  "n": "***",
  "p": "***",
  "q": "***",
  "qi": "***",
  "use": "sig",
  "alg": "RS512",
  "kid": "***"
}
```

