feat: add block-no-verify PreToolUse hook to .claude/settings.json

## Add `block-no-verify` to prevent agents from bypassing git hooks

**Problem**

`.claude/settings.json` currently configures `UserPromptSubmit` and `PostToolUse` hooks but does not include a `PreToolUse` hook to prevent AI agents from running `git commit` or `git push` with the hook-bypass flag. When an agent uses this flag, it silently skips pre-commit, commit-msg, and pre-push hooks — defeating linting, formatting, and test-before-commit checks entirely.

**Solution**

Add [`block-no-verify`](https://github.com/tupe12334/block-no-verify) as a `PreToolUse` Bash hook:

```json
{
  "hooks": {
    "PreToolUse": [
      {
        "matcher": "Bash",
        "hooks": [{ "type": "command", "command": "npx block-no-verify@1.1.2" }]
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

`block-no-verify` reads `tool_input.command` from the Claude Code hook stdin payload, detects the hook-bypass flag across all git subcommands, and exits 2 to block the tool call before it runs. The existing hooks are preserved unchanged.

I'm happy to open a PR for this if the maintainers are interested.

bug: `parentSpanContext` param creates an anonymous parent span (Typescript)

### Describe the bug

I want to create a span using a given traceID, and according to your docs, I should do it via `parentSpanContext` options param.
While it does work by creating an "anonymous" parent - a parent trace that doesn't have name, input, output or metadata. There is also no way to access the parent trace to update its name etc. 

See below is what I see in the web UI

<img width="898" height="369" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5bfdb86c-e0d5-441b-9db1-dfba4a47aea5" />

### Steps to reproduce

You may use the code from your [official doc](https://langfuse.com/docs/observability/features/trace-ids-and-distributed-tracing), with the span name slightly changed

```
import { createTraceId, startObservation } from "@langfuse/tracing";

const externalId = "support-ticket-54321";

// Generate a valid, deterministic traceId from the external ID
const langfuseTraceId = await createTraceId(externalId);

// You can now start a new trace with this ID
const rootSpan = startObservation(
  "simple-test-span",
  {},
  {
    parentSpanContext: {
      traceId: langfuseTraceId,
      spanId: "0123456789abcdef", // A valid 16 hexchar string; value is irrelevant as parent span does not exist but only used for inheritance
      traceFlags: 1, // mark trace as sampled
    },
  }
);

// Later, you can regenerate the same traceId to score or retrieve the trace
const scoringTraceId = await createTraceId(externalId);
// scoringTraceId will be the same as langfuseTraceId
```

### Langfuse Cloud or self-hosted?

Langfuse Cloud

### If self-hosted, what version are you running?

_No response_

### SDK and integration versions

Latest version Otel and Langfuse

### Additional information

_No response_

### Are you interested in contributing a fix for this bug?

No
